The paper deals with pseudocodewords, which are related to error-correcting codes, and uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The Bethe permanent is a concept from statistical physics (cs.DS), which is also mentioned in the paper. The paper also discusses the properties of block matrices, which are relevant to computer science (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
